15/12/2010
NEW YORK, United States -- The UN Security Council on Tuesday (December 14th) urged Greek and Turkish Cypriots to accelerate talks to reunify their divided island, stressing that "a solution is within reach." The Council expressed concern about the pace of negotiations in recent months and urged "decisive progress in the near future".
The Council also adopted a resolution extending the mandate of the UN peacekeeping mission in Cyprus through June 15th 2011.
(AP, UN News Centre, Anadolu news agency - 14/12/10)
